{"parse":{"title":"Holocaust teaching controversy of 2007","pageid":14462000,"revid":823977936,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Holocaust teaching controversy of 2007</b> was a hoax sparked by sensationalist claims mainly circulated in <a href=\"/wiki/Emails\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Emails\">emails</a> which claimed that teaching of the <a href=\"/wiki/Holocaust\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Holocaust\">Holocaust</a> had been banned in British schools because of fears that this could offend <a href=\"/wiki/Muslim\" title=\"Muslim\">Muslim</a> pupils.<sup id=\"cite_ref-news.bbc.co.uk_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-news.bbc.co.uk-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> These claims were false, but inspired by real events.\n</p><p>The emails alleged that the ban had been put in place because of fears that such teaching could \"offend\" <a href=\"/wiki/Muslim\" title=\"Muslim\">Muslim</a> pupils, claiming that \"the Muslim population\" denied the Holocaust. On 2 April 2007, the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Daily_Mail\" title=\"Daily Mail\">Daily Mail</a></i> started the story on the subject with \"Schools [plural, contrary to the findings of the report] are dropping the Holocaust from history lessons to avoid offending Muslim pupils, a Government backed study has revealed.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Following this, the tabloid <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Post\" title=\"New York Post\">New York Post</a> ran an article headlined \"U.K. SCHOOLS' SICKENING SILENCE\" in which the writer asserted the statement \"may be the scariest sentence I ever read\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The main medium for the claims, however, was a <a href=\"/wiki/Chain_email\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Chain email\">chain email</a>. The emails led some to email the <a href=\"/wiki/BBC\" title=\"BBC\">BBC</a> enquiring as to whether the facts contained in the email were true. In fact teaching of the Holocaust is mandatory in English <a href=\"/wiki/State_school\" title=\"State school\">state schools</a>, except in <a href=\"/wiki/Academy_(English_school)\" title=\"Academy (English school)\">academies</a>, and has not been banned elsewhere in the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Kingdom\" title=\"United Kingdom\">United Kingdom</a>.\n</p><p>After email messages continued to circulate into 2008 the British government Schools Secretary <a href=\"/wiki/Ed_Balls\" title=\"Ed Balls\">Ed Balls</a> decided to write to <a href=\"/wiki/Embassy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Embassy\">embassies</a> in the country and to the world media to refute the allegation that schools had banned or were reluctant to teach about the Holocaust.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<table class=\"toccolours\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; font-size: 85%; background:#ffffoo; color:black; width:23em; max-width: 25%;\" cellspacing=\"5\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: centre;\">\n<p>The most popular version of the email reads as follows:<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><b>In Memoriam</b>\n</p><p>Recently, this week, UK removed The Holocaust from its school curriculum because it \"offended\" the Muslim population which claims it never occurred. This is a frightening portent of the fear that is gripping the world and how easily each country is giving into it.\n</p><p>It is now more than 60 years after the Second World War in Europe ended. This e-mail is being sent as a memorial chain, in memory of the six million Jews, 20 million Russians, 10 million Christians and 1,900 Catholic priests who were murdered, massacred, raped, burned, starved and humiliated with the German and Russia [sic] peoples looking the other way!\n</p><p>Now, more than ever, with Iran , among others, claiming the Holocaust to be \"a myth,\" it is imperative to make sure the world never forgets.\n</p><p>This e-mail is intended to reach 40 million people worldwide!\n</p><p>Join us and be a link in the memorial chain and help us distribute it around the world. Please send this e-mail to 10 people you know and ask them to continue the memorial chain.\n</p><p>Please don't just delete it. It will only take you a minute to pass this along - Thanks!\n</p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: centre;\">\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Report\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Report</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Report\">Report</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Holocaust_teaching_controversy_of_2007&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Report\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The emails were based upon a wide-ranging report which the <a href=\"/wiki/Department_for_Education_and_Skills_(United_Kingdom)\" title=\"Department for Education and Skills (United Kingdom)\">Department for Education and Skills</a> commissioned from the <a href=\"/wiki/Historical_Association\" title=\"Historical Association\">Historical Association</a>, a group which promotes the study of history. This report suggested that teachers may avoid emotive and controversial periods of history, but did not recommend that they do. The report went on to give an example of \"a northern city\" in which a history department had  \"recently avoided selecting the Holocaust as a topic for <a href=\"/wiki/GCSE\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"GCSE\">GCSE</a> coursework for fear of confronting <a href=\"/wiki/Antisemitism\" title=\"Antisemitism\">anti-Semitic</a> sentiment and Holocaust denial among some Muslim pupils\";<sup id=\"cite_ref-news.bbc.co.uk_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-news.bbc.co.uk-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> it was also noted that, in another school, the Holocaust had been taught in spite of \"anti-Semitic sentiment among some pupils\" but that study of the <a href=\"/wiki/Crusades\" title=\"Crusades\">Crusades</a> had been avoided because of the contrast to the stories with which Muslim pupils were raised. In no case was it suggested that avoiding causing offence to Holocaust deniers should be an aim.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Holocaust_teaching_controversy_of_2007&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Holocaust_Educational_Trust\" title=\"Holocaust Educational Trust\">Holocaust Educational Trust</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Holocaust_denial\" title=\"Holocaust denial\">Holocaust denial</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Holocaust_teaching_controversy_of_2007&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-news.bbc.co.uk-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-news.bbc.co.uk_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-news.bbc.co.uk_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/education/6563429.stm\">\"Holocaust 'ban' e-mail confusion\"</a>. <i>BBC News</i>. 17 April 2007<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">4 May</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=BBC+News&amp;rft.atitle=Holocaust+%27ban%27+e-mail+confusion&amp;rft.date=2007-04-17&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F1%2Fhi%2Feducation%2F6563429.stm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHolocaust+teaching+controversy+of+2007\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Clark, Laura (2 April 2007). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/pages/live/articles/news/news.html?in_article_id=445979&amp;in_page_id=1770\">\"Teachers drop the Holocaust to avoid offending Muslims\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Mail_Online\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mail Online\">Mail Online</a></i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Mail+Online&amp;rft.atitle=Teachers+drop+the+Holocaust+to+avoid+offending+Muslims&amp;rft.date=2007-04-02&amp;rft.aulast=Clark&amp;rft.aufirst=Laura&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailymail.co.uk%2Fpages%2Flive%2Farticles%2Fnews%2Fnews.html%3Fin_article_id%3D445979%26in_page_id%3D1770&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHolocaust+teaching+controversy+of+2007\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Rubin, Barry (April 8, 2007). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.nypost.com/seven/04082007/postopinion/opedcolumnists/u_k__schools_sickening_silence_opedcolumnists_barry_rubin.htm?page=0\">\"U.K. SCHOOLS' SICKENING SILENCE\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Post\" title=\"New York Post\">New York Post</a></i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=New+York+Post&amp;rft.atitle=U.K.+SCHOOLS%27+SICKENING+SILENCE&amp;rft.date=2007-04-08&amp;rft.aulast=Rubin&amp;rft.aufirst=Barry&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nypost.com%2Fseven%2F04082007%2Fpostopinion%2Fopedcolumnists%2Fu_k&#95;_schools_sickening_silence_opedcolumnists_barry_rubin.htm%3Fpage%3D0&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHolocaust+teaching+controversy+of+2007\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/education/7226778.stm\">\"UK government acts on hoax e-mail\"</a>. <i>BBC News</i>. 4 February 2008<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">4 May</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=BBC+News&amp;rft.atitle=UK+government+acts+on+hoax+e-mail&amp;rft.date=2008-02-04&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F1%2Fhi%2Feducation%2F7226778.stm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHolocaust+teaching+controversy+of+2007\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.snopes.com/politics/religion/holocaust.asp\">Urban Legends Reference Pages: Holocaust Teaching Ban</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Holocaust_teaching_controversy_of_2007&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.history.org.uk/secondary/resource/780/the-teach-report\">\"The T.E.A.C.H. report: Teaching Emotive and Controversial History 3-19\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(pdf)</span>. <a href=\"/wiki/The_Historical_Association\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Historical Association\">The Historical Association</a>. 2007<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-02-04</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+T.E.A.C.H.+report%3A+Teaching+Emotive+and+Controversial+History+3-19&amp;rft.pub=The+Historical+Association&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.org.uk%2Fsecondary%2Fresource%2F780%2Fthe-teach-report&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHolocaust+t